attributes.description: We get a little serious this week, but not too much. But maybe MORE later! It'll make sense, we promise.

attributes.title: WE ARE DIGIMUPPS
attributes.description: We could celebrate the fans in this description, but instead I'm going to complain that our ethernet Chromecast adapter didn't work. Ain't that some shit.Also our capture computer crashed so we had to use our stream footage, so sorry about the format.

attributes.title: WE ARE RAD
attributes.description: Fine crop of art this week, mighty fine. Spoole announced he was leaving last night though so there's not a whole lot of sad Spoole stuff going on just yet. Don't worry, it'll be in next week's episode... just in time for him to be gone forever. RIP Spoole.

attributes.title: WE ARE TENDER

attributes.title: WE ARE GLITCHED OUT
attributes.description: Not to spoil anything, but this episode has a shocking revelation about Adam's face.

attributes.title: WE ARE TITANS
attributes.description: The fanart is increasing every week. This pleases us. Please the allmighty Funhaus!

attributes.title: WE ARE ASSHOLES
attributes.description: We know how to give someone a warm welcome. Just shove a controller in their hands and then scream at them for several minutes at a time.

attributes.title: WE ARE POUTY, PRECIOUS, PROUD
attributes.description: You guys are getting really good at this fanart thing. We should make a show about it.

attributes.title: WE ARE STARKILLER BASE
attributes.description: CORRECTION: The fan art depicting Adam with James and Bruce puppets was actually made by Nate Boyles (@AnimNate)!We'll be turning in our Fan Art badge and gun tomorrow.

attributes.title: WE ARE OVERWATCHING
attributes.description: This week's is a very special Fan Show as we realize we can just make the comments first and actually have time to talk about them! Stay tuned next week for a very comment-y Fan Show.

attributes.title: WE ARE ENGAGING
attributes.description: Welcome to a comment-heavy Fan Show, wherein people comment about comments. Tune in next week for comments about comments about comments.

attributes.title: WE ARE POP IDOLS
attributes.description: This week's Fan Show is a little less heavy, so don't worry about Millennial problems this week! Nothing but sweet, sweet fan art and comments.

attributes.title: WE ARE HEISTERS
attributes.description: Thirty fan shows in the books! We've lived, laughed, loved, and mocked a bunch of Millennials. What's in store for the next dirty thirty?FULLONPORNOGRAPHY.

attributes.title: WE ARE CENTAURS
attributes.description: It's a post-PAX fan show, meaning I didn't have enough time to find all the fan art I usually do. That means a slower-paced, more relaxed show! I'm pitching it as a good thing.

attributes.title: WE ARE SMIRKING
attributes.description: Mighty fine crop of fan art this week. You folks out there been doing a real good job.*chews on a stalk of hay*Real good.

attributes.title: WE ARE SNIPERS
attributes.description: Pachaeeewwwww. One shot, one kill. Elyse gotcha.

attributes.title: WE ARE SERENADED
attributes.description: Fan Show has a new home! Turns out it's the same home as the show that happens right next to this. Weird how that turns out huh.

attributes.title: WE ARE GREASY
attributes.description: Fan Show (Fan Haus?) continues to evolve. Now it sounds good AND people can fire questions at us!

attributes.title: WE ARE ATTRACTIVE
attributes.description: That Google Slides feature is a real lifesaver, just stop spamming those questions OK.

attributes.title: WE ARE NINJA TURTLES

attributes.title: WE ARE SPOOKED

attributes.title: WE ARE COPS
attributes.description: The Fan Art Show is dead. All hail The Dude Soup Post Show! It's the same damn thing, really.

attributes.title: WE ARE SURGEONS
attributes.description: At last! Our fantasy of cutting open celebrities and diddling their organs finally has a visual representation! Thanks guys. You know what we live for.
